name: Pentaerythritol

Estimating the contribution of each additional hydroxyl group to the melting point is complex, but for simplicity, if we consider each hydroxy group to add approximately the same melting point increment, we can try to estimate it from related compounds. Assuming a diminishing return for each additional group due to sterics and already high level of hydrogen bonding, we might estimate each additional hydroxyl group could add somewhat less, perhaps around 65 degrees.
